{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 160°C. Grease and line a springform cake tin (25 cm). Grease the baking paper lining the tin and dust with 1 tablespoon of the extra cocoa powder, ensuring the bottom and sides of tin are covered. Set baking tin aside.","Place dark chocolate into mixing bowl and melt <nobr>3 min\/50°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then melt for a further <nobr>2-3 min\/50°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>, or until chocolate has fully melted. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place figs into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add hazelnuts and almonds and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, or until a roughly chopped consistency is achieved.","Add flour, cinnamon, ginger, pepper (optional), nutmeg, chilli powder (optional) and 40 g cocoa powder and combine <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add reserved melted chocolate and combine <nobr>5 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer mixture into a large bowl and set aside.","Place sugar and honey into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer into the large bowl and combine well with spatula.","Transfer mixture into prepared cake tin and smooth over the top. Bake for 30-35 minutes (160°C). The centre will feel soft but will firm as the panforte cools.","Allow to cool for 15 minutes, then run a knife around the edge between baking paper and tin. Remove baking paper from panforte and transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely.","Once cooled, dust panforte with 1 tablespoon extra cocoa powder, then serve immediately or transfer into a sealable storage container to store until use."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["butter, for greasing","40 g cocoa powder (70% cocoa), plus extra 2 tbsp for dusting","100 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa), broken into pieces","160 g dried figs","150 g hazelnuts, roasted and skins removed","120 g blanched almonds","110 g plain f